231
00:09:40,546 --> 00:09:43,164
This city used to be different.
People used to feel safe.

232
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:44,415
Afraid we're gonna be next?

233
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:45,916
<font color="#d900d9">(SIREN WAILING)</font>

234
00:09:45,918 --> 00:09:47,668
<i>He gained the attention</i>
<i>of the law...</i>

235
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:49,203
Freeze!

236
00:09:49,205 --> 00:09:50,921
Bow down, hands up.

237
00:09:50,923 --> 00:09:52,473
<font color="#d900d9">(CLANK)</font>

238
00:09:55,894 --> 00:10:00,147
<i>And earn notice from enemies</i>
<i>he didn't yet know existed.</i>

239
00:10:00,149 --> 00:10:02,683
A modern day Robin Hood.

240
00:10:02,685 --> 00:10:05,436
Jason Brodeur.

241
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:07,104
Adam Hunt.

242
00:10:07,106 --> 00:10:08,822
Warren Patel.

243
00:10:08,824 --> 00:10:11,358
Tell me you see a connection,
Moira.

244
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,626
He's not targeting the rich.

245
00:10:12,628 --> 00:10:14,578
No, he's not.

246
00:10:14,580 --> 00:10:15,996
He's targeting the list.

247
00:10:19,734 --> 00:10:23,854
<i>Secrets and lies were critical</i>
<i>to survival,</i>

248
00:10:23,856 --> 00:10:25,072
<i>so to the public,</i>

249
00:10:25,074 --> 00:10:26,891
<i>he was the rich playboy</i>
<i>he had always been.</i>

250
00:10:26,893 --> 00:10:28,509
I miss Tequila!

251
00:10:28,511 --> 00:10:30,294
<font color="#d900d9">(CHEERING)</font>

252
00:10:30,296 --> 00:10:32,446
<i>To the Russian</i> Bratva,

253
00:10:32,448 --> 00:10:33,631
<i>he was a captain.</i>

254
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,015
<i>And after earning</i>
<i>their trust...</i>

255
00:10:35,017 --> 00:10:36,417
Pleased to meet you.

256
00:10:36,419 --> 00:10:38,769
<i>They provided</i>
<i>valuable information</i>

257
00:10:38,771 --> 00:10:40,771
about the criminal underground.

258
00:10:40,773 --> 00:10:43,941
<i>But to Oliver's family,</i>
<i>he was a ghost.</i>

259
00:10:43,943 --> 00:10:46,443
I felt closer to you
when you were dead.

260
00:10:46,445 --> 00:10:49,263
Look, I know it was hell
where you were,

261
00:10:49,265 --> 00:10:51,282
but it was hell here, too.

262
00:10:51,284 --> 00:10:52,766
You gotta let me in, Ollie.

263
00:10:52,768 --> 00:10:55,519
You gotta let <i>someone</i> in.

264
00:10:55,521 --> 00:10:57,104
<font color="#808080">MOIRA:</font> Oliver.

265
00:10:57,106 --> 00:10:59,123
I wanna introduce you
to someone.

266
00:11:03,161 --> 00:11:04,161
<font color="#808080">OLIVER:</font> What do I call you?

267
00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:05,212
<font color="#808080">JOHN:</font> Diggle's good.

268
00:11:05,214 --> 00:11:08,299
<i>To his new bodyguard</i>
<i>John Diggle...</i>

269
00:11:08,301 --> 00:11:09,583
So...

270
00:11:09,585 --> 00:11:11,719
<i>Oliver would be an extremely</i>
<i>difficult assignment.</i>

271
00:11:11,721 --> 00:11:13,254
You're ex-military?
Yes, sir.

272
00:11:13,256 --> 00:11:16,423
105th Airborne
out of Kandahar. Retired.

273
00:11:16,425 --> 00:11:17,808
I don't want there to be
any confusion, Mr. Queen.

274
00:11:17,810 --> 00:11:19,793
My ability to keep you from harm
will outweigh your comfort.

275
00:11:19,795 --> 00:11:20,878
<font color="#d900d9">(CAR DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)</font>

276
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:23,463
<font color="#d900d9">(CAR HORNS HONK,
TIRES SCREECH)</font>

277
00:11:24,649 --> 00:11:27,151
<i>Years before,</i>
<i>Diggle's brother was murdered</i>

278
00:11:27,153 --> 00:11:30,237
<i>by a vicious assassin</i>
<i>called Deadshot,</i>

279
00:11:30,239 --> 00:11:33,640
<i>who had recently returned</i>
<i>to Starling City.</i>

280
00:11:33,642 --> 00:11:34,975
<font color="#d900d9">(GUNSHOT)</font>

281
00:11:34,977 --> 00:11:36,443
Aah!
<font color="#d900d9">(WOMAN SCREAMS)</font>

282
00:11:36,445 --> 00:11:38,812
<i>Oliver faced off</i>
<i>with the killer...</i>

283
00:11:47,455 --> 00:11:48,639
Uhh!
<font color="#d900d9">(THUD)</font>

284
00:11:48,641 --> 00:11:50,958
<i>And took him out,</i>

285
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:52,326
<i>but not before</i>

286
00:11:52,328 --> 00:11:54,962
<i>one of Deadshot's</i>
<i>signature poison-laced bullets</i>

287
00:11:54,964 --> 00:11:56,830
<i>ended up in Diggle.</i>

288
00:11:56,832 --> 00:11:59,166
<i>After saving</i>
<i>his bodyguard's life,</i>

289
00:11:59,168 --> 00:12:03,020
<i>Oliver decided it was time</i>
<i>to let him in on his secret.</i>

290
00:12:03,022 --> 00:12:04,355
You're that vigilante.

291
00:12:04,357 --> 00:12:06,940
Starling City is dying.

292
00:12:06,942 --> 00:12:10,844
It is being poisoned
by a criminal elite

293
00:12:10,846 --> 00:12:14,398
who don't care
who they hurt.

294
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,699
And what are you gonna do?

295
00:12:15,701 --> 00:12:17,651
Take 'em all down
by your lonesome?

296
00:12:17,653 --> 00:12:19,853
No, I want you to join me.

297
00:12:19,855 --> 00:12:21,572
Here's the security footage

298
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:23,290
from the Exchange building
shooting.

299
00:12:23,292 --> 00:12:26,026
<i>While investigating</i>
<i>the Deadshot incident,</i>

300
00:12:26,028 --> 00:12:28,629
<i>Detective Lance made</i>
<i>a shocking discovery.</i>

301
00:12:28,631 --> 00:12:29,830
Hey, whoa, whoa, whoa.
What?

302
00:12:29,832 --> 00:12:32,800
Wait, go back 10 seconds.
What is that?

303
00:12:32,802 --> 00:12:34,885
<font color="#d900d9">(TAPS BUTTON)</font>
I'll be damned.

304
00:12:36,805 --> 00:12:38,472
<font color="#808080">OLIVER:</font>
What the hell is going on?!

305
00:12:38,474 --> 00:12:39,640
<font color="#808080">THEA:</font> What's happening?!
Oliver Queen, you're under arrest

306
00:12:39,642 --> 00:12:41,141
on suspicion
of obstruction of justice,

307
00:12:41,143 --> 00:12:42,343
aggravated assault...
What?!

308
00:12:42,345 --> 00:12:44,812
Acting as a vigilante,
and murder.

309
00:12:44,814 --> 00:12:46,096
Who's your attorney,
Mr. Queen?

310
00:12:46,098 --> 00:12:49,183
<i>The accusation made for</i>
<i>an unlikely alliance...</i>

311
00:12:49,185 --> 00:12:50,434
Dinah Laurel Lance, Your Honor.

312
00:12:50,436 --> 00:12:52,586
<i>And drove a wedge</i>
<i>between father and daughter.</i>

313
00:12:52,588 --> 00:12:54,772
You hate the hood
and you hate Oliver,

314
00:12:54,774 --> 00:12:57,408
and you want more than anything
for them to be the same person.

315
00:12:57,410 --> 00:12:59,193
<i>Oliver managed</i>
<i>to beat a polygraph.</i>

316
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:01,862
Are you the man in this picture?
No.

317
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:04,048
<i>The truth he</i> did <i>tell...</i>

318
00:13:04,050 --> 00:13:06,033
I didn't want to talk about what
happened to me on the island

319
00:13:06,035 --> 00:13:08,452
because the people that were
there tortured me.

320
00:13:08,454 --> 00:13:09,920
<i>Had an effect on Laurel.</i>

321
00:13:09,922 --> 00:13:12,222
<font color="#d900d9">(GASPS)</font>

322
00:13:12,224 --> 00:13:13,874
How did you survive this?

323
00:13:13,876 --> 00:13:16,126
There were times
when I wanted to die.

324
00:13:16,128 --> 00:13:17,644
<font color="#d900d9">(GASPS)</font>

325
00:13:17,646 --> 00:13:21,548
In the end, there was something
I wanted more.

326
00:13:28,423 --> 00:13:31,975
You don't...
Laurel, you don't have to go.

327
00:13:33,094 --> 00:13:35,896
<i>House arrest provided Oliver</i>
<i>an opportunity</i>

328
00:13:35,898 --> 00:13:38,232
<i>to prove he wasn't the Hood,</i>

329
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:39,599
<i>with a little help...</i>

330
00:13:42,287 --> 00:13:43,487
<i>From Diggle</i>

331
00:13:43,489 --> 00:13:44,988
<i>as the vigilante.</i>

332
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:47,574
An arms dealer was attacked
across town tonight

333
00:13:47,576 --> 00:13:49,042
by the vigilante.
In light of that,

334
00:13:49,044 --> 00:13:51,495
all charges against your son
are being dropped.

335
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:52,946
Thank you.

336
00:13:52,948 --> 00:13:54,631
<i>Once he was free,</i>

337
00:13:54,633 --> 00:13:56,616
<i>Oliver and Diggle went</i>
<i>back to work.</i>

338
00:13:56,618 --> 00:13:57,784
Ow! Uhh!

339
00:13:57,786 --> 00:13:59,553
Variable acceleration.

340
00:13:59,555 --> 00:14:00,838
Fighters work
at the same pace.

341
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:03,390
You switch it up, throw your
opponent off his game.

342
00:14:03,392 --> 00:14:05,259
That was nice.
Where'd you learn that?

343
00:14:05,261 --> 00:14:07,060
His name was Yao Fei.

344
00:14:12,817 --> 00:14:15,769
<font color="#d900d9">(THUNDERCLAP)</font>

345
00:14:15,771 --> 00:14:17,020
<i>After the shipwreck,</i>

346
00:14:17,022 --> 00:14:20,807
<i>Oliver landed</i>
<i>on the island of Lian Yu.</i>

347
00:14:20,809 --> 00:14:23,026
<i>He soon discovered...</i>

348
00:14:23,028 --> 00:14:24,778
Aah! Aah!

349
00:14:24,780 --> 00:14:26,997
<i>He was not alone.</i>

350
00:14:26,999 --> 00:14:28,499
<i>First he met Yao Fei...</i>

351
00:14:28,501 --> 00:14:29,833
<font color="#d900d9">(SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)</font>

352
00:14:29,835 --> 00:14:31,168
<i>Ex-Chinese military</i>

353
00:14:31,170 --> 00:14:35,172
<i>exiled to the island</i>
<i>for a crime he didn't commit.</i>

354
00:14:35,174 --> 00:14:37,040
<i>Also on the island?</i>

355
00:14:37,042 --> 00:14:39,576
Do you know what
this island is named?

356
00:14:39,578 --> 00:14:41,328
Lian Yu.

357
00:14:41,330 --> 00:14:42,829
Mandarin for "Purgatory""

358
00:14:42,831 --> 00:14:46,166
<i>a mysterious militia</i>
<i>with bad intentions.</i>

359
00:14:46,168 --> 00:14:47,801
Aah!

360
00:14:49,003 --> 00:14:51,522
<i>After Yao rescued Oliver...</i>

361
00:14:57,178 --> 00:15:00,364
<i>He sent him to meet</i>
<i>another ally.</i>

362
00:15:01,349 --> 00:15:05,586
<font color="#d900d9">(GASPS)</font> Twitch and I will open
your throat.

363
00:15:06,821 --> 00:15:08,155
<font color="#d900d9">(STRAINED VOICE)</font>
Yao Fei sent me here,

364
00:15:08,157 --> 00:15:10,157
and I'm pretty sure it wasn't
so you could kill me.

365
00:15:10,159 --> 00:15:13,877
<i>Slade Wilson was Australian</i>
<i>secret intelligence service,</i>

366
00:15:13,879 --> 00:15:17,164
<i>stranded on the island</i>
<i>after a failed operation</i>

367
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:18,966
<i>to extricate Yao Fei.</i>

368
00:15:18,968 --> 00:15:21,201
Everybody is in this life
for themselves.

369
00:15:21,203 --> 00:15:23,670
Learn that
at Australian spy school?

370
00:15:23,672 --> 00:15:26,890
No. I learned that here.

371
00:15:26,892 --> 00:15:31,711
<i>He taught Oliver that to</i>
<i>survive and escape the island,</i>

372
00:15:31,713 --> 00:15:33,931
<i>he would have to fight.</i>

373
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:35,882
You have no skill,

374
00:15:35,884 --> 00:15:38,101
no strength,

375
00:15:38,103 --> 00:15:39,353
no training.

376
00:15:39,355 --> 00:15:42,573
I told you,
I'm not a soldier.

377
00:15:45,827 --> 00:15:47,945
Aah!

378
00:15:47,947 --> 00:15:50,397
<font color="#d900d9">(LAUGHS)</font>
Aah!

379
00:15:50,399 --> 00:15:51,582
<font color="#d900d9">(PANTING)</font>

380
00:15:51,584 --> 00:15:54,518
There might be a fighter
inside of you after all.

381
00:15:57,088 --> 00:15:58,572
You know, one of these days,
you're gonna be straight with me

382
00:15:58,574 --> 00:16:00,290
about what really happened
on that island.

383
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:01,792
Absolutely.

384
00:16:01,794 --> 00:16:03,343
Aah!
Aah!

385
00:16:03,345 --> 00:16:04,911
But not today.

386
00:16:04,913 --> 00:16:06,213
<i>Diggle was the only one</i>

387
00:16:06,215 --> 00:16:09,216
<i>who knew the truth</i>
<i>about Oliver's double life,</i>

388
00:16:09,218 --> 00:16:12,269
<i>but there was another</i>
<i>who Oliver turned to regularly.</i>

389
00:16:12,271 --> 00:16:13,971
Felicity Smoak?

390
00:16:15,807 --> 00:16:16,890
<i>Felicity Smoak...</i>

391
00:16:16,892 --> 00:16:19,643
<i>Queen Consolidated's</i>
<i>I.T. superstar.</i>

392
00:16:19,645 --> 00:16:22,646
I was at my coffee shop
surfing the web,

393
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:24,114
and I spilled a latte on it.

394
00:16:24,116 --> 00:16:25,499
These look like bullet holes.

395
00:16:25,501 --> 00:16:27,234
My coffee shop is
in a bad neighborhood.

396
00:16:27,236 --> 00:16:29,570
So a friend of mine is running
a scavenger hunt.

397
00:16:29,572 --> 00:16:31,705
I first need to get
through this.

398
00:16:31,707 --> 00:16:34,741
This is a military-grade
cryptographic security protocol.

399
00:16:34,743 --> 00:16:36,910
My buddy Kevin is starting
an energy drink company.

400
00:16:36,912 --> 00:16:39,279
Could you please do
a spectral analysis?

401
00:16:39,281 --> 00:16:41,782
If it's an energy drink,

402
00:16:41,784 --> 00:16:43,584
why is it in a syringe?

403
00:16:43,586 --> 00:16:45,802
I ran out of sports bottles.

404
00:16:46,754 --> 00:16:47,971
<i>Felicity was also a resource</i>

405
00:16:47,973 --> 00:16:50,924
<i>for Oliver's stepfather</i>
<i>Walter Steele.</i>

406
00:16:50,926 --> 00:16:53,460
I was hoping you could
look into something for me.

407
00:16:53,462 --> 00:16:54,611
Discreetly.

408
00:16:54,613 --> 00:16:56,013
I'm your girl.

409
00:16:57,649 --> 00:17:02,402
<i>When Walter found a mysterious</i>
<i>diary in his wife's possession,</i>

410
00:17:02,404 --> 00:17:05,072
<i>Felicity helped him decode it.</i>

411
00:17:06,074 --> 00:17:08,909
<i>It was information</i>
<i>too dangerous to hold.</i>

412
00:17:08,911 --> 00:17:10,193
<font color="#808080">MOIRA:</font> Let me talk to him.

413
00:17:10,195 --> 00:17:12,913
I think we're past the point
of conversation, Moira,

414
00:17:12,915 --> 00:17:15,949
which means something
must be done about it.

415
00:17:15,951 --> 00:17:18,335
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Please help me welcome
Mr. Malcolm Merlyn.

416
00:17:18,337 --> 00:17:21,922
<i>Malcolm Merlyn was a titan</i>
<i>of Starling City industry.</i>

417
00:17:21,924 --> 00:17:24,124
<i>He was also Tommy's father.</i>

418
00:17:24,126 --> 00:17:25,825
My wife would've liked you,
Laurel.

419
00:17:25,827 --> 00:17:28,011
Their relationship was complex.

420
00:17:28,013 --> 00:17:29,963
Well, I wish I would've
known her.

421
00:17:29,965 --> 00:17:31,998
She passed away before
Tommy and I became friends.

422
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,100
She was killed, Laurel.

423
00:17:33,102 --> 00:17:34,568
There's no need
to be polite about it.

424
00:17:34,570 --> 00:17:37,604
<i>Merlyn was also</i>
<i>a man with secrets...</i>

425
00:17:37,606 --> 00:17:40,641
<i>Secrets he would do anything</i>
<i>to protect.</i>

426
00:17:40,643 --> 00:17:41,841
<font color="#d900d9">(GRUNTS)</font>

427
00:17:41,843 --> 00:17:43,193
<font color="#808080">MALCOLM:</font> It's done.

428
00:17:43,195 --> 00:17:44,645
And he won't be harmed?

429
00:17:44,647 --> 00:17:47,013
Nor will he ever discover your
involvement. You have my word.

430
00:17:47,015 --> 00:17:48,365
What's done is done.

431
00:17:48,367 --> 00:17:49,683
No, Moira.

432
00:17:49,685 --> 00:17:51,685
It's just beginning.

433
00:17:53,037 --> 00:17:55,188
<font color="#d900d9">(MAN, MODULATED VOICE)</font>
We must send a message.

434
00:17:55,190 --> 00:17:58,375
<font color="#d900d9">(ARROWS WHOOSH)</font>
<font color="#d900d9">(SQUISH)</font>

435
00:17:58,377 --> 00:18:00,911
<i>When the dark archer</i>
<i>first appeared,</i>

436
00:18:00,913 --> 00:18:02,796
<i>it seemed he was just</i>
<i>an imitator</i>

437
00:18:02,798 --> 00:18:04,864
<i>in a different color hood.</i>

438
00:18:04,866 --> 00:18:08,001
<i>But when he drew Oliver</i>
<i>into a fight,</i>

439
00:18:08,003 --> 00:18:10,870
<i>his purpose was</i>
<i>curiously specific.</i>

440
00:18:10,872 --> 00:18:12,673
I know about the list,

441
00:18:12,675 --> 00:18:15,225
and the man who authored it
wants you dead!

442
00:18:21,933 --> 00:18:23,233
Aah!

443
00:18:26,237 --> 00:18:28,488
Uhh! Aah! Uhh!

444
00:18:28,490 --> 00:18:33,226
Oliver knew he was dealing with
<i>somebody more than a copycat.</i>

445
00:18:33,228 --> 00:18:37,247
The other archer told me that
somebody compiled the list.

446
00:18:37,249 --> 00:18:40,701
I always assumed
it was my father.

447
00:18:40,703 --> 00:18:43,737
I think there's someone else
out there,

448
00:18:43,739 --> 00:18:48,175
someone who's more of a danger
than the archer.

449
00:18:51,512 --> 00:18:55,665
And I am gonna take him down.

450
00:19:00,538 --> 00:19:03,071
<i>While Oliver was focused</i>
<i>solely on the list...</i>

451
00:19:03,073 --> 00:19:07,376
Leo Mueller,
you have failed this city.

452
00:19:07,378 --> 00:19:08,911
<i>Others expected more of him.</i>

453
00:19:08,913 --> 00:19:10,662
Maybe you can
make a difference

454
00:19:10,664 --> 00:19:12,881
if you think beyond the scope
of those pages.

455
00:19:12,883 --> 00:19:13,949
I'm sure your father
wouldn't mind.

456
00:19:13,951 --> 00:19:15,050
No, you don't get it.

457
00:19:15,052 --> 00:19:17,219
My father died
so that I could live.

458
00:19:17,221 --> 00:19:20,472
Every name that I cross off
this list honors that sacrifice.

459
00:19:20,474 --> 00:19:22,724
Oliver, there's more than
one way to save this city.

460
00:19:22,726 --> 00:19:24,125
Not for me.

461
00:19:24,127 --> 00:19:26,762
It sounds like you have a narrow
definition of being a hero.

462
00:19:26,764 --> 00:19:28,129
I'm not a hero.

463
00:19:28,131 --> 00:19:29,464
<i>Hero or not,</i>

464
00:19:29,466 --> 00:19:33,235
<i>more of his missions took him</i>
<i>outside of the list.</i>

465
00:19:33,237 --> 00:19:34,353
Aah!

466
00:19:34,355 --> 00:19:36,438
<i>He took down drug dealers...</i>

467
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:38,323
Enjoy
the fruits of your labor.

468
00:19:38,325 --> 00:19:39,825
<font color="#d900d9">(GROANS)</font>

469
00:19:39,827 --> 00:19:41,693
<i>Psychopathic murderers...</i>

470
00:19:42,979 --> 00:19:45,080
<i>A family of thieves.</i>

471
00:19:45,082 --> 00:19:46,915
Drop your weapons!
I got this!

472
00:19:46,917 --> 00:19:48,500
No! Uhh!

473
00:19:48,502 --> 00:19:50,536
<i>And at times,</i>
<i>he showed compassion</i>

474
00:19:50,538 --> 00:19:54,339
<i>towards those driven to crime</i>
<i>by the city his father failed.</i>

475
00:19:54,341 --> 00:19:55,674
It wasn't his fault.

476
00:19:55,676 --> 00:19:58,794
<font color="#d900d9">(BREATHES HEAVILY)</font>
I turned my son into this.

477
00:19:58,796 --> 00:20:01,797
If your dad could've
seen you this week,

478
00:20:01,799 --> 00:20:03,582
the way you cared about
the people he had hurt,

479
00:20:03,584 --> 00:20:06,101
the way you stepped up
to try to help them...

480
00:20:06,103 --> 00:20:08,103
I'd say he'd be
pretty damn honored.

481
00:20:10,189 --> 00:20:11,673
I can't imagine

482
00:20:11,675 --> 00:20:13,892
you want the death
of an innocent young woman

483
00:20:13,894 --> 00:20:16,695
on your hands,
not with your principles.

484
00:20:16,697 --> 00:20:18,063
Aah!

485
00:20:21,017 --> 00:20:23,118
<font color="#808080">YAO FEI:</font> No!
Hey!

486
00:20:23,120 --> 00:20:24,152
Uhh!

487
00:20:24,154 --> 00:20:26,288
<i>Shado was Yao Fei's daughter,</i>

488
00:20:26,290 --> 00:20:29,190
<i>brought from mainland China</i>
<i>to Lian Yu</i>

489
00:20:29,192 --> 00:20:31,627
to use as leverage against Yao.

490
00:20:31,629 --> 00:20:33,045
No.

491
00:20:33,047 --> 00:20:36,214
<i>It soon became apparent that</i>
<i>Shado was not an ideal captive.</i>

492
00:20:36,216 --> 00:20:37,799
Let the girl go.

493
00:20:37,801 --> 00:20:39,551
<font color="#808080">FYERS:</font> Kill her!
No!

494
00:20:39,553 --> 00:20:42,203
<i>And she proved she was</i>
<i>her father's daughter.</i>

495
00:20:48,711 --> 00:20:51,480
Shado, along with Slade Wilson,

496
00:20:51,482 --> 00:20:54,499
<i>trained Oliver to fight.</i>

497
00:20:54,501 --> 00:20:55,984
<i>She coached him in skills</i>

498
00:20:55,986 --> 00:20:57,853
<i>she had learned</i>
<i>from her father.</i>

499
00:20:57,855 --> 00:20:59,738
Showoff.

500
00:20:59,740 --> 00:21:01,723
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Missile one locked
on the jet's heat trail.

501
00:21:01,725 --> 00:21:03,859
<font color="#808080">FYERS:</font> Prepare to launch
on my mark.

502
00:21:03,861 --> 00:21:05,060
<i>When the island militia</i>

503
00:21:05,062 --> 00:21:07,162
<i>attempted to down</i>
<i>a commercial airliner...</i>

504
00:21:07,164 --> 00:21:09,081
We need to reprogram
the missile.

505
00:21:09,083 --> 00:21:11,249
<i>Oliver and his allies...</i>
<font color="#d900d9">(BEEPS)</font>

506
00:21:11,251 --> 00:21:12,701
<font color="#d900d9">(MISSILE WHISTLING)</font>

507
00:21:14,921 --> 00:21:16,254
Let her go.

508
00:21:16,256 --> 00:21:17,906
<i>And when tested,</i>

509
00:21:17,908 --> 00:21:21,093
<i>Oliver put everything he had</i>
<i>learned from Slade and Shado</i>

510
00:21:21,095 --> 00:21:22,544
<i>into practice.</i>

511
00:21:22,546 --> 00:21:23,845
Uhh!

512
00:21:28,217 --> 00:21:29,935
I got your message.

513
00:21:29,937 --> 00:21:33,221
Is there a reason we can't
do this face-to-face?

514
00:21:37,060 --> 00:21:38,427
<i>Oliver, as the vigilante,</i>

515
00:21:38,429 --> 00:21:40,829
<i>began covertly helping</i>
<i>Laurel Lance</i>

516
00:21:40,831 --> 00:21:43,031
<i>to defend people</i>
<i>the law couldn't protect.</i>

517
00:21:43,033 --> 00:21:44,232
What's in here?

518
00:21:44,234 --> 00:21:47,285
Leverage. Enough to help save
Peter Declan's life.

519
00:21:47,287 --> 00:21:51,156
As an attorney, I never would've
gotten a file like this.

520
00:21:51,158 --> 00:21:54,743
I always thought the law was
sacred. You fixed everything.

521
00:21:54,745 --> 00:21:56,211
Now what do you think?

522
00:21:56,213 --> 00:21:57,462
I think there's
too many people in this city

523
00:21:57,464 --> 00:21:59,280
who only care about
themselves.

524
00:21:59,282 --> 00:22:01,883
They need someone like you.

525
00:22:03,386 --> 00:22:04,836
<i>Her connection to the Hood</i>

526
00:22:04,838 --> 00:22:07,122
<i>complicated</i>
<i>Laurel's relationships</i>

527
00:22:07,124 --> 00:22:08,957
<i>with her father...</i>

528
00:22:08,959 --> 00:22:10,142
He's a damn criminal,
and you've worked with him.

529
00:22:10,144 --> 00:22:11,292
That makes you an accessory.

530
00:22:11,294 --> 00:22:13,595
I am trying to save
an innocent man's life.

531
00:22:14,897 --> 00:22:16,631
No.

532
00:22:16,633 --> 00:22:18,850
You're breaking the law.

533
00:22:18,852 --> 00:22:20,068
<i>And her boyfriend.</i>

534
00:22:20,070 --> 00:22:22,303
So you met up with
the hood guy? Knowingly?

535
00:22:22,305 --> 00:22:23,555
Laurel, he's a murderer.

536
00:22:23,557 --> 00:22:24,806
You sound like my father.

537
00:22:24,808 --> 00:22:26,908
Well, I hate to break it to you,
but he's right.

538
00:22:26,910 --> 00:22:29,194
She's been working with
the hood guy.

539
00:22:29,196 --> 00:22:33,982
And there's some sort of
infatuation thing going on here.

540
00:22:33,984 --> 00:22:36,051
I...
fix this.

541
00:22:36,053 --> 00:22:39,404
Before it becomes something
that's unfixable.

542
00:22:40,256 --> 00:22:42,758
<i>Oliver had trouble</i>
<i>being honest,</i>

543
00:22:42,760 --> 00:22:44,492
<i>but that didn't</i>
<i>stop Felicity...</i>

544
00:22:44,494 --> 00:22:46,478
Hi.
Hi.

545
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:48,680
<i>From coming to him for help.</i>

546
00:22:48,682 --> 00:22:50,549
Can I trust you?

547
00:22:50,551 --> 00:22:53,018
You've dropped some
fairly ridiculous lies on me,

548
00:22:53,020 --> 00:22:54,352
and...

549
00:22:54,354 --> 00:22:57,439
Yet I still feel like
I can trust you.

550
00:22:57,441 --> 00:22:59,307
You can trust me.

551
00:23:01,110 --> 00:23:02,728
Then I have something
to show you.

552
00:23:08,101 --> 00:23:09,735
Where'd you get it?

553
00:23:09,737 --> 00:23:12,537
From your stepfather.

554
00:23:12,539 --> 00:23:15,907
He said it belongs
to your mother.

555
00:23:17,477 --> 00:23:20,028
This is
your father's notebook.

556
00:23:20,030 --> 00:23:23,331
He kept a list of all the people
in Starling City

557
00:23:23,333 --> 00:23:24,583
who owed him favors.

558
00:23:24,585 --> 00:23:27,869
I've been researching some of
those names online,

559
00:23:27,871 --> 00:23:30,756
and, uh,
they're not good people.

560
00:23:33,843 --> 00:23:37,545
The only way
to keep this family safe

561
00:23:37,547 --> 00:23:40,899
is for everyone in it
to stop asking questions,

562
00:23:40,901 --> 00:23:43,318
including you, Oliver.

563
00:23:44,821 --> 00:23:48,857
<i>But there were still</i>
<i>too many questions left to ask.</i>

564
00:23:48,859 --> 00:23:50,642
I made it clear to him
persuasively

565
00:23:50,644 --> 00:23:52,911
that his plans endanger
the undertaking.

566
00:23:52,913 --> 00:23:55,831
I didn't have to make
the usual threats.

567
00:23:55,833 --> 00:23:56,948
<font color="#808080">MALCOLM:</font> Excellent.

568
00:23:56,950 --> 00:23:59,901
<i>Oliver was concerned</i>
<i>about his mother...</i>

569
00:23:59,903 --> 00:24:01,069
What's the Undertaking?

570
00:24:01,071 --> 00:24:02,521
I don't know.

571
00:24:02,523 --> 00:24:05,406
But with all this talk
about threats, it can't be good.

572
00:24:05,408 --> 00:24:08,760
<i>And determined to find out</i>
<i>everything she knew.</i>

573
00:24:08,762 --> 00:24:10,128
What are you gonna do?

574
00:24:14,917 --> 00:24:16,084
<font color="#d900d9">(GASPS)</font>

575
00:24:16,086 --> 00:24:17,886
Moira Queen,

576
00:24:17,888 --> 00:24:20,755
you have failed this city.

577
00:24:27,773 --> 00:24:29,541
Please don't kill me.

578
00:24:29,543 --> 00:24:31,977
Do you know anything
about the Undertaking?

579
00:24:31,979 --> 00:24:33,111
I am a mother.

580
00:24:33,113 --> 00:24:35,330
Please don't take me
from my children.

581
00:24:35,332 --> 00:24:38,467
<i>Oliver couldn't help</i>
<i>but show his mother mercy.</i>

582
00:24:38,469 --> 00:24:40,252
I'm not gonna hurt you.

583
00:24:43,590 --> 00:24:45,007
<i>He should've known better.</i>

584
00:24:45,009 --> 00:24:47,392
<font color="#d900d9">(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)</font>

585
00:24:47,394 --> 00:24:48,810
<i>After he escaped...</i>
<font color="#d900d9">(CAR ALARM CHIRPS)</font>

586
00:24:48,812 --> 00:24:51,063
<i>He went to the one person</i>
<i>at Queen Consolidated</i>

587
00:24:51,065 --> 00:24:53,015
<i>he could trust.</i>
Whoa!

588
00:24:53,017 --> 00:24:54,766
<font color="#d900d9">(STRAINED VOICE)</font> I'm not gonna
hurt you, Felicity.

589
00:24:54,768 --> 00:24:56,968
How do you know my name?
Because you know my name.

590
00:24:56,970 --> 00:24:59,821
Everything about you just became
so unbelievably clear.

591
00:24:59,823 --> 00:25:01,106
<font color="#d900d9">(EXHALES)</font>

592
00:25:01,108 --> 00:25:03,825
<i>The Starling City Vigilante</i>
<i>attacked Mrs. Queen...</i>

593
00:25:03,827 --> 00:25:05,810
<font color="#808080">FELICITY:</font> Excuse me.

594
00:25:05,812 --> 00:25:08,247
Can you help me?
He's... really heavy.

595
00:25:09,282 --> 00:25:10,815
<font color="#808080">FELICITY:</font> I should've
taken him to a hospital.

596
00:25:10,817 --> 00:25:13,151
Felicity, listen. Trust me.
He'll be fine.

597
00:25:13,153 --> 00:25:15,587
He's been through a lot worse
than this.

598
00:25:15,589 --> 00:25:17,839
<i>Once Oliver was stable,</i>

599
00:25:17,841 --> 00:25:20,709
<i>Diggle and Felicity</i>
<i>addressed the obvious.</i>

600
00:25:20,711 --> 00:25:23,095
I was thinking all this
would be more of a shock.

601
00:25:23,097 --> 00:25:25,130
Oliver brought me a laptop
riddled with bullet holes,

602
00:25:25,132 --> 00:25:26,965
had me trace the black arrow,

603
00:25:26,967 --> 00:25:30,302
and research a company involved
in armored car heists.

604
00:25:30,304 --> 00:25:32,521
I maybe blonde,
but I'm not <i>that</i> blonde.

605
00:25:32,523 --> 00:25:35,941
<font color="#d900d9">(MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY)</font>

606
00:25:35,943 --> 00:25:38,360
I guess I didn't die. Again.

607
00:25:39,395 --> 00:25:40,812
Cool.

608
00:25:40,814 --> 00:25:44,566
<i>Felicity was officially</i>
<i>part of the team.</i>

609
00:25:47,704 --> 00:25:51,657
<i>The Glades is a notoriously</i>
<i>rough side of Starling City...</i>

610
00:25:51,659 --> 00:25:53,041
Hey!

611
00:25:53,043 --> 00:25:56,545
<i>Known as a breeding ground</i>
<i>for all manner of criminal.</i>

612
00:25:57,697 --> 00:25:58,880
<font color="#d900d9">(SCOFFS)</font>

613
00:26:00,917 --> 00:26:02,501
<font color="#808080">THEA:</font> I found the dirtbag.

614
00:26:02,503 --> 00:26:04,253
His name is Roy Harper.

615
00:26:04,255 --> 00:26:05,404
<font color="#d900d9">(KNOCKS ON DOOR)</font>

616
00:26:05,406 --> 00:26:06,972
<font color="#808080">ROY:</font> How'd you know
where I lived?

617
00:26:06,974 --> 00:26:08,640
A little thing called
the Internet.

618
00:26:08,642 --> 00:26:11,893
<i>Thea Queen was not</i>
<i>a cooperative victim.</i>

619
00:26:11,895 --> 00:26:13,845
You know, you showed
some real sac coming down here,

620
00:26:13,847 --> 00:26:15,113
the Glades in the middle
of the night...

621
00:26:15,115 --> 00:26:18,150
You must not know the value
of a vintage purse.

622
00:26:18,152 --> 00:26:20,435
Hey, can I give you
some advice?

623
00:26:20,437 --> 00:26:21,987
Stay out of the Glades.

624
00:26:21,989 --> 00:26:24,990
<i>As it turns out,</i>
<i>Roy's advice was sound.</i>

625
00:26:24,992 --> 00:26:26,108
Where's downtown at?

626
00:26:26,110 --> 00:26:27,225
I-I-I don't know.

627
00:26:27,227 --> 00:26:29,244
Maybe you can give us
some directions.

628
00:26:29,246 --> 00:26:31,062
Or better yet, some money.

629
00:26:36,235 --> 00:26:37,502
<font color="#d900d9">(PANTING)</font> Ow.

630
00:26:37,504 --> 00:26:39,421
You're bleeding!
Yeah, I know.

631
00:26:39,423 --> 00:26:40,672
That's what happens
when you get stabbed.

632
00:26:40,674 --> 00:26:43,742
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font>
This could sting a little.

633
00:26:43,744 --> 00:26:45,910
Oh, don't tell me
a tough gangbanger like yourself

634
00:26:45,912 --> 00:26:47,713
is afraid of
a tiny little needle.

635
00:26:47,715 --> 00:26:50,182
Well, just think about
something else.

636
00:26:50,184 --> 00:26:51,683
Like what? <font color="#d900d9">(INHALES SHARPLY)</font>

637
00:26:54,437 --> 00:26:57,522
<i>Thea was charmed</i>
<i>by Roy's bravery...</i>

638
00:26:57,524 --> 00:26:59,057
<font color="#808080">ROY:</font>
I was waiting for this.

639
00:26:59,059 --> 00:27:01,026
Waiting for what?

640
00:27:01,028 --> 00:27:02,927
<i>But not by his life</i>
<i>as a petty crook.</i>

641
00:27:02,929 --> 00:27:04,896
This is home, sweet home
for me.

642
00:27:04,898 --> 00:27:06,097
You either starve
or you do things

643
00:27:06,099 --> 00:27:08,150
that mean you're lucky enough
to make it to 21.

644
00:27:08,152 --> 00:27:10,118
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Roy Harper?
Yeah?

645
00:27:10,120 --> 00:27:11,603
Uhh!
Roy!

646
00:27:11,605 --> 00:27:13,822
<i>A deranged vigilante</i>
<i>called the Savior</i>

647
00:27:13,824 --> 00:27:16,158
<i>looked to make an example</i>
<i>of Roy.</i>

648
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:17,743
More on the story
out of the Glades.

649
00:27:17,745 --> 00:27:20,212
The kidnapper seems to have
another victim.

650
00:27:20,214 --> 00:27:22,631
You know him?
Uh, Roy. He's my friend. <font color="#d900d9">(SNIFFLES)</font>

651
00:27:22,633 --> 00:27:26,551
I promise you
he's gonna be okay.

652
00:27:26,553 --> 00:27:27,836
Felicity, show me a map...
<font color="#d900d9">(TAPS KEY)</font>

653
00:27:27,838 --> 00:27:29,004
Of sites of the abductions

654
00:27:29,006 --> 00:27:30,756
and where we've seen the signal
so far. <font color="#d900d9">(TYPING)</font>

655
00:27:30,758 --> 00:27:32,591
<i>Diggle and Felicity traced</i>
<i>Savior's location</i>

656
00:27:32,593 --> 00:27:35,477
<i>to Starling City's</i>
<i>abandoned subway.</i>

657
00:27:37,797 --> 00:27:39,130
Don't do it!

658
00:27:41,267 --> 00:27:42,934
<i>After Oliver rescued him,</i>

659
00:27:42,936 --> 00:27:45,771
<i>Roy reconsidered</i>
<i>his life's purpose.</i>

660
00:27:45,773 --> 00:27:47,439
<font color="#808080">ROY:</font> I thought
I was gonna die.

661
00:27:47,441 --> 00:27:49,608
But you didn't.
Yeah, because of him.

662
00:27:49,610 --> 00:27:52,444
I can't go back to the way
things were, Thea.

663
00:27:52,446 --> 00:27:55,313
I c-can't just go back
to being nothing.

664
00:27:55,315 --> 00:27:56,581
I can't explain it,

665
00:27:56,583 --> 00:27:59,984
but it feels like my life is
connected to his.

666
00:27:59,986 --> 00:28:03,789
<i>The incident provided clarity</i>
<i>for Oliver as well.</i>

667
00:28:03,791 --> 00:28:04,989
I've seen that map before.

668
00:28:04,991 --> 00:28:07,592
It's an old map of
a decommissioned subway line.

669
00:28:07,594 --> 00:28:09,878
It runs underneath the low-rent
district of the city.

670
00:28:09,880 --> 00:28:13,665
<font color="#808080">OLIVER:</font> It was right in front
of our faces the entire time.

671
00:28:13,667 --> 00:28:16,101
My father, the other archer,
the Undertaking...

672
00:28:16,103 --> 00:28:19,671
Whatever the plan is, it's all
connected to the Glades.

673
00:28:20,807 --> 00:28:23,692
<font color="#808080">MALCOLM:</font> The Undertaking,
which we set for ourselves,

674
00:28:23,694 --> 00:28:26,695
is only months from fruition.

675
00:28:26,697 --> 00:28:29,848
There's hope on the horizon
for everyone in Starling.

676
00:28:29,850 --> 00:28:31,032
<font color="#d900d9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

677
00:28:31,034 --> 00:28:33,535
We won't fail this city.

678
00:28:33,537 --> 00:28:36,571
And I think I speak
for everyone here

679
00:28:36,573 --> 00:28:39,374
when I say we're all with you,
Malcolm.

680
00:28:39,376 --> 00:28:42,494
<i>But privately,</i>
<i>Moira had misgivings...</i>

681
00:28:42,496 --> 00:28:43,795
I wanna get out.

682
00:28:43,797 --> 00:28:47,966
That's, uh, a lot to confide
in me, Moira.

683
00:28:47,968 --> 00:28:49,367
<i>As did a colleague.</i>

684
00:28:49,369 --> 00:28:52,537
I've gone along with this
for as long as I can stomach.

685
00:28:52,539 --> 00:28:55,390
Frank Chen recommended you.

686
00:28:55,392 --> 00:28:57,592
He said you could help us
with our problem.

687
00:28:57,594 --> 00:28:59,711
How can we be of assistance?

688
00:28:59,713 --> 00:29:01,430
Malcolm Merlyn.

689
00:29:01,432 --> 00:29:04,065
I want you to kill him
for me.

690
00:29:04,067 --> 00:29:06,050
<font color="#d900d9">(MALCOLM, AMPLIFIED VOICE)</font>
The true humanitarian

691
00:29:06,052 --> 00:29:09,354
in the Merlyn family
was my wife Rebecca.

692
00:29:09,356 --> 00:29:13,275
I like to think that if the man
who murdered her knew her,

693
00:29:13,277 --> 00:29:16,394
he would've helped her to
her car, made sure she was safe,

694
00:29:16,396 --> 00:29:19,531
instead of stealing her purse
and shooting her.

695
00:29:20,399 --> 00:29:23,084
<font color="#d900d9">(BEEP, ALARM BLARING)</font>

696
00:29:23,086 --> 00:29:25,420
<font color="#d900d9">(SMACK)</font> Ladies and gentlemen,
please exit calmly...

697
00:29:25,422 --> 00:29:28,123
<i>Malcolm Merlyn was not</i>
<i>an easy target.</i>

698
00:29:28,125 --> 00:29:29,508
Tommy.

699
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:32,243
Come with me.

700
00:29:33,513 --> 00:29:36,247
<i>He would not go down</i>
<i>without a fight...</i>

701
00:29:37,633 --> 00:29:39,768
<i>A fact that took his son</i>
<i>by surprise.</i>

702
00:29:39,770 --> 00:29:41,686
Wait!

703
00:29:41,688 --> 00:29:43,054
Let's go!

704
00:29:43,056 --> 00:29:45,273
How did you know
how to do that?

705
00:29:45,275 --> 00:29:47,275
What?
Kill.

706
00:29:47,277 --> 00:29:50,562
<font color="#d900d9">(EXPLOSION)</font>

707
00:29:50,564 --> 00:29:52,764
<font color="#d900d9">(RAPID GUNFIRE)</font>

708
00:29:54,233 --> 00:29:55,367
Dad!

709
00:29:55,369 --> 00:29:57,536
<font color="#d900d9">(GASPING)</font>

710
00:29:58,771 --> 00:30:00,605
<i>Oliver arrived in time.</i>

711
00:30:00,607 --> 00:30:01,740
Stay back.

712
00:30:01,742 --> 00:30:04,342
I'm not here to hurt you
or your father.

713
00:30:04,344 --> 00:30:05,744
I said stay back.

714
00:30:05,746 --> 00:30:07,078
If you don't let me
help you now,

715
00:30:07,080 --> 00:30:09,781
he's dead before
anybody gets here!

716
00:30:09,783 --> 00:30:12,417
Why should I trust you?!

717
00:30:12,419 --> 00:30:15,587
<i>But there was no time left</i>
<i>for secrets.</i>

718
00:30:18,558 --> 00:30:21,459
'Cause you always have.

719
00:30:21,461 --> 00:30:23,795
Oliver.

720
00:30:30,202 --> 00:30:32,821
<font color="#d900d9">(GASPS AND GROANS)</font>

721
00:30:32,823 --> 00:30:35,540
Dad. Oh.
Take it easy.

722
00:30:35,542 --> 00:30:37,442
<i>Thanks to Oliver...</i>

723
00:30:37,444 --> 00:30:38,827
The Vigilante saved you.

724
00:30:38,829 --> 00:30:39,944
He did?

725
00:30:39,946 --> 00:30:42,530
<i>Malcolm Merlyn was alive.</i>

726
00:30:42,532 --> 00:30:45,083
<i>But thanking him wasn't</i>
<i>foremost in Tommy's mind.</i>

727
00:30:45,085 --> 00:30:46,551
I know you have
a lot of questions.

728
00:30:46,553 --> 00:30:48,887
Yeah.

729
00:30:48,889 --> 00:30:50,088
<font color="#d900d9">(INHALES DEEPLY)</font>

730
00:30:50,090 --> 00:30:52,907
Yeah, but for now,
just the one.

731
00:30:56,145 --> 00:30:59,130
Were you ever gonna
tell me?

732
00:30:59,132 --> 00:31:00,732
No.

733
00:31:00,734 --> 00:31:03,067
<i>Tommy's distrust of Oliver</i>

734
00:31:03,069 --> 00:31:05,103
quickly grew to include Laurel.

735
00:31:05,105 --> 00:31:06,688
When you first got home,

736
00:31:06,690 --> 00:31:09,774
I didn't think that you had
changed much.

737
00:31:09,776 --> 00:31:13,561
But you have, and...

738
00:31:13,563 --> 00:31:14,746
It's nice to see.

739
00:31:14,748 --> 00:31:16,948
<font color="#d900d9">(WHISPERS)</font> Thank you.

740
00:31:19,118 --> 00:31:22,203
<font color="#d900d9">(THUNDERCLAP)</font>

741
00:31:22,205 --> 00:31:25,423
You still love her,
don't you?

742
00:31:25,425 --> 00:31:26,758
It doesn't matter how I feel,

743
00:31:26,760 --> 00:31:30,912
because of what I do,
I could never be with her.

744
00:31:30,914 --> 00:31:32,764
So you don't have anything
to be afraid of.

745
00:31:32,766 --> 00:31:36,017
She is <i>never...</i>

746
00:31:36,019 --> 00:31:38,920
ever going to know
my secret.

747
00:31:38,922 --> 00:31:41,439
It doesn't matter.
She knows.

748
00:31:41,441 --> 00:31:43,424
I know.

749
00:31:43,426 --> 00:31:48,746
But if she ever found out
who you really are...

750
00:31:48,748 --> 00:31:50,765
She would choose you.

751
00:31:50,767 --> 00:31:53,284
<font color="#d900d9">(LAUREL WHISPERING)</font>
You can't be serious.

752
00:31:53,286 --> 00:31:54,819
I'm not sure that I'm ready
for the kind of commitment

753
00:31:54,821 --> 00:31:55,954
that you're looking for.

754
00:31:55,956 --> 00:31:59,040
And I don't want to hurt you
in the long run, so...

755
00:31:59,042 --> 00:32:00,208
<font color="#d900d9">(VOICE BREAKS)</font> You're lying.

756
00:32:00,210 --> 00:32:02,443
I am not a liar.

757
00:32:02,445 --> 00:32:05,680
If you've changed,
and I know that you've changed,

758
00:32:05,682 --> 00:32:07,114
you would never do this.

759
00:32:07,116 --> 00:32:08,299
Well, then I guess

760
00:32:08,301 --> 00:32:10,221
I haven't changed as much
as we all thought then.

761
00:32:12,988 --> 00:32:14,055
<i>And Tommy's rejection...</i>

762
00:32:14,057 --> 00:32:16,140
Will you please
go talk to Tommy for me?

763
00:32:16,142 --> 00:32:18,977
<i>Produced</i>
<i>a self-fulfilling prophecy.</i>

764
00:32:18,979 --> 00:32:20,245
And say what?

765
00:32:20,247 --> 00:32:22,230
Say that
you and I are over,

766
00:32:22,232 --> 00:32:24,298
that you're not
still in love with me.

767
00:32:25,768 --> 00:32:28,386
I can't do that.

768
00:32:28,388 --> 00:32:30,321
Why not?

769
00:32:30,323 --> 00:32:34,158
Because it wouldn't be true.

770
00:32:48,457 --> 00:32:50,391
<font color="#808080">MOIRA:</font>
Thank you for coming, Frank.

771
00:32:50,393 --> 00:32:53,678
<i>Merlyn's survival forced Moira</i>
<i>to cover her tracks.</i>

772
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:54,829
Malcolm knows.

773
00:32:54,831 --> 00:32:56,497
<font color="#d900d9">(WHISPERS)</font> What?
I had no choice

774
00:32:56,499 --> 00:32:58,850
but to turn over what
they've discovered... <font color="#d900d9">(EXHALES DEEPLY)</font>

775
00:32:58,852 --> 00:33:00,835
The money that you paid
the Triad to assassinate him.

776
00:33:00,837 --> 00:33:02,353
<font color="#d900d9">(ARROW WHOOSHES)</font> The money I...
<font color="#d900d9">(INHALES SHARPLY)</font>

777
00:33:02,355 --> 00:33:04,138
Moira!

778
00:33:05,173 --> 00:33:08,943
Mr. Merlyn thanks you
for your loyalty.

779
00:33:08,945 --> 00:33:11,779
<i>Moira's paranoia</i>
<i>began to boil over...</i>

780
00:33:11,781 --> 00:33:12,864
<font color="#d900d9">(SOBS)</font>

781
00:33:12,866 --> 00:33:15,867
You lied to me.
We had a deal!

782
00:33:15,869 --> 00:33:17,235
<i>And so did she.</i>

783
00:33:17,237 --> 00:33:19,704
You promised if I cooperated
with the Undertaking,

784
00:33:19,706 --> 00:33:20,872
Walter wouldn't be harmed!

785
00:33:20,874 --> 00:33:23,458
He hasn't been.
I'm a man of my word, Moira.

786
00:33:23,460 --> 00:33:25,159
I think we both know better
than that.

787
00:33:25,161 --> 00:33:26,527
Turn on the camera.

788
00:33:29,715 --> 00:33:31,883
Oh, Walter.

789
00:33:31,885 --> 00:33:33,918
Like you said, Moira,
we have an agreement.

790
00:33:33,920 --> 00:33:35,202
Walter would stay
in my custody

791
00:33:35,204 --> 00:33:38,673
until the Undertaking
was complete.

792
00:33:38,675 --> 00:33:40,241
We're both in this together.

793
00:33:40,243 --> 00:33:42,727
<i>And Oliver learned</i>
<i>the startling truth</i>

794
00:33:42,729 --> 00:33:44,045
<i>about his mother.</i>

795
00:33:44,047 --> 00:33:46,097
She's working with
Malcolm Merlyn.

796
00:33:48,216 --> 00:33:51,069
And they're
planning something.

797
00:33:52,488 --> 00:33:54,522
Something...

798
00:33:54,524 --> 00:33:56,190
Terrible.

799
00:34:03,818 --> 00:34:05,257
Hey, mom.

800
00:34:05,258 --> 00:34:07,041
<i>After uncovering</i>
<i>his mother's involvement</i>

801
00:34:07,043 --> 00:34:08,425
<i>with Merlyn's plot,</i>

802
00:34:08,427 --> 00:34:10,995
<i>Oliver confronted her</i>
<i>yet again.</i>

803
00:34:10,997 --> 00:34:12,446
Tell me the truth.

804
00:34:12,448 --> 00:34:13,580
I don't know what you mean.

805
00:34:13,582 --> 00:34:14,849
I think you do.

806
00:34:14,851 --> 00:34:16,851
Couple of months ago, when
I showed you Dad's notebook,

807
00:34:16,853 --> 00:34:18,585
you seemed to know
something.

808
00:34:18,587 --> 00:34:20,587
<i>When she continued</i>
<i>to be evasive...</i>

809
00:34:20,589 --> 00:34:22,790
You need to stop asking
these things.

810
00:34:22,792 --> 00:34:24,424
I <i>can't.</i>

811
00:34:24,426 --> 00:34:25,693
I <i>need</i> to know.
<font color="#d900d9">(ELECTRICITY POWERS DOWN)</font>

812
00:34:25,695 --> 00:34:27,728
<i>Oliver used</i>
<i>more drastic measures.</i>

813
00:34:27,730 --> 00:34:28,863
<font color="#d900d9">(DART WHOOSHES)</font>

814
00:34:28,865 --> 00:34:30,564
Oh.

815
00:34:30,566 --> 00:34:31,649
Oliver.

816
00:34:31,651 --> 00:34:33,367
<font color="#d900d9">(DART WHOOSHES)</font>
Ohh.

817
00:34:33,369 --> 00:34:35,653
<font color="#d900d9">(BREATHES HEAVILY)</font>

818
00:34:36,488 --> 00:34:39,990
Moira Queen,
you have failed this city.

819
00:34:39,992 --> 00:34:42,993
Please, do not hurt my son.

820
00:34:42,995 --> 00:34:45,663
Tell me what the Undertaking is,
and I won't have to.

821
00:34:46,781 --> 00:34:48,299
<font color="#808080">MOIRA:</font> No! <font color="#d900d9">(GASPS)</font>

822
00:34:48,301 --> 00:34:49,800
Uhh!
No!

823
00:34:49,802 --> 00:34:53,220
Malcolm is planning
to level the Glades!

824
00:34:53,222 --> 00:34:55,455
How?
There's a device.

825
00:34:55,457 --> 00:34:58,392
He says that it could cause
an earthquake.

826
00:34:58,394 --> 00:35:00,811
Why would you get involved
in something like this?

827
00:35:00,813 --> 00:35:02,396
My husband.

828
00:35:02,398 --> 00:35:05,299
He was lost. He...

829
00:35:05,301 --> 00:35:08,302
His decisions left me
vulnerable to Malcolm.

830
00:35:08,304 --> 00:35:09,436
And I had no choice.

831
00:35:09,438 --> 00:35:12,356
I had to protect my family
and my children.

832
00:35:12,358 --> 00:35:14,441
This device, where is it?

833
00:35:14,443 --> 00:35:15,793
I don't know.

834
00:35:15,795 --> 00:35:17,545
If you don't tell me,
I can't stop Merlyn.

835
00:35:17,547 --> 00:35:19,029
Oh, you can't stop him.

836
00:35:19,031 --> 00:35:20,531
It's too late.

837
00:35:20,533 --> 00:35:24,318
<i>Finally, Oliver understood</i>
<i>his true mission.</i>

838
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:25,686
It's the Undertaking.

839
00:35:25,688 --> 00:35:29,540
I was just treating the symptoms
while the disease festered.

840
00:35:29,542 --> 00:35:33,794
I stop the Undertaking,
I wipe out the disease.

841
00:35:35,013 --> 00:35:38,415
Merlyn's plan is what I returned
from the island to stop.

842
00:35:41,553 --> 00:35:43,520
For the past five years,

843
00:35:43,522 --> 00:35:46,473
under the threat for my life
and the lives of my family...

844
00:35:46,475 --> 00:35:48,892
<i>Moira finally decided</i>
<i>to come clean.</i>

845
00:35:48,894 --> 00:35:50,394
I have been complicit

846
00:35:50,396 --> 00:35:53,197
in an undertaking
with one horrible purpose...

847
00:35:53,199 --> 00:35:56,533
to destroy the Glades
and everyone in it.

848
00:35:57,986 --> 00:36:02,689
The architect of this nightmare
<i>is Malcolm Merlyn.</i>

849
00:36:02,691 --> 00:36:04,858
<font color="#d900d9">(SCREAMS)</font>

850
00:36:04,860 --> 00:36:07,211
Yes, and I have proof
that he has killed dozens

851
00:36:07,213 --> 00:36:09,079
in pursuit of this madness.

852
00:36:09,081 --> 00:36:12,499
Is it true?
Did you kill all those people?

853
00:36:14,002 --> 00:36:16,053
I did what I had to do.

854
00:36:17,372 --> 00:36:20,140
Malcolm Merlyn,
you are under arrest!

855
00:36:20,142 --> 00:36:21,375
Don't move!

856
00:36:23,762 --> 00:36:25,562
Dad, no!

857
00:36:28,233 --> 00:36:30,934
Stay back.
I don't wanna hurt you.

858
00:36:30,936 --> 00:36:33,320
You can't,

859
00:36:33,322 --> 00:36:35,555
and you can't stop me.

860
00:36:37,725 --> 00:36:38,942
This red line here

861
00:36:38,944 --> 00:36:41,228
is a known fault that runs
right below the Glades.

862
00:36:41,230 --> 00:36:42,663
For about a mile,
the fault runs underneath

863
00:36:42,665 --> 00:36:44,064
the old
10th Street subway line.

864
00:36:44,066 --> 00:36:45,199
Dollars to doughnuts,

865
00:36:45,201 --> 00:36:47,234
the seismic device is
somewhere along there.

866
00:36:47,236 --> 00:36:48,735
<font color="#d900d9">(CELL PHONE CHIMES AND BUZZES)</font>

867
00:36:48,737 --> 00:36:50,587
I know were Merlyn is
keeping the device.

868
00:36:50,589 --> 00:36:54,074
I need someone I can trust
to deactivate the device.

869
00:36:54,076 --> 00:36:55,376
<font color="#d900d9">(SIRENS WAILING)</font>

870
00:36:55,378 --> 00:36:57,344
<font color="#808080">MAN ON TV:</font> Earlier today,
Moira Queen, C.E.O. of...

871
00:36:57,346 --> 00:37:01,799
<i>News of the impending disaster</i>
<i>had already reached the Glades.</i>

872
00:37:01,801 --> 00:37:05,419
<i>As Detective Lance searched</i>
<i>for the device...</i>

873
00:37:05,421 --> 00:37:06,470
<font color="#d900d9">(MAN ON TV
SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

874
00:37:06,472 --> 00:37:08,889
<i>Everyone prepared</i>
<i>for the worst.</i>

875
00:37:08,891 --> 00:37:10,257
<font color="#d900d9">(MAN, AMPLIFIED VOICE)</font>
Proceed out of the Glades

876
00:37:10,259 --> 00:37:12,976
in an orderly manner.

877
00:37:12,978 --> 00:37:17,731
<i>Oliver and Diggle moved in</i>
<i>to take Merlyn down.</i>

878
00:37:17,733 --> 00:37:20,934
Welcome, gentlemen.
I've been waiting for you.

879
00:37:20,936 --> 00:37:23,770
I wanted to see you watch
your city die.

880
00:37:29,327 --> 00:37:30,878
Uhh! Aah!

881
00:37:30,880 --> 00:37:32,279
Aah!

882
00:37:32,281 --> 00:37:35,833
<font color="#d900d9">(BEEPING)</font>
<font color="#d900d9">(GASPS)</font>

883
00:37:35,835 --> 00:37:37,000
<font color="#808080">FELICITY:</font>
You should see something

884
00:37:37,002 --> 00:37:38,635
that looks like a circuit board.
Okay.

885
00:37:38,637 --> 00:37:40,671
Felicity talked Detective Lance
<i>through disarming the weapon...</i>

886
00:37:40,673 --> 00:37:42,056
Do you see a timer?

887
00:37:42,058 --> 00:37:44,808
<font color="#d900d9">(CONTINUES BEEPING)</font>
7 minutes.

888
00:37:44,810 --> 00:37:45,959
Okay.

889
00:37:45,961 --> 00:37:48,795
<i>While Oliver battled</i>
<i>to stop its damage.</i>

890
00:37:55,070 --> 00:37:56,820
Cut the blue one.
All right, I got it. I got it.

891
00:37:56,822 --> 00:37:57,938
<font color="#d900d9">(SNIPS)</font>

892
00:37:57,940 --> 00:37:59,990
Oh!
<font color="#d900d9">(WHIRRING)</font>

893
00:37:59,992 --> 00:38:01,158
<font color="#d900d9">(BEEPING RESUMES)</font>

894
00:38:01,160 --> 00:38:02,826
Holy God.

895
00:38:02,828 --> 00:38:05,028
<font color="#d900d9">(TIRES SCREECH)</font>
Roy!

896
00:38:05,030 --> 00:38:06,497
Thea tracked down Roy Harper...

897
00:38:06,499 --> 00:38:09,249
Roy, stop! Look!
<font color="#d900d9">(PEOPLE SCREAMING AT ONCE)</font>

898
00:38:09,251 --> 00:38:11,919
The device is about to go off
any second!

899
00:38:11,921 --> 00:38:14,588
<i>But she couldn't persuade him</i>
<i>to abandon his home.</i>

900
00:38:14,590 --> 00:38:15,923
I leave any of them behind.

901
00:38:15,925 --> 00:38:18,825
Look, I-I know you said
you have something to prove,

902
00:38:18,827 --> 00:38:20,660
but you're not the vigilante.

903
00:38:20,662 --> 00:38:22,546
I can't do this unless
I know you're safe.

904
00:38:22,548 --> 00:38:25,933
Then you better haul ass
out of here, too.

905
00:38:25,935 --> 00:38:28,102
With chaos erupting everywhere,

906
00:38:28,104 --> 00:38:32,189
<i>Oliver had one final chance to</i>
<i>prevent complete destruction.</i>

907
00:38:32,191 --> 00:38:35,058
Don't struggle.
It's over.

908
00:38:35,060 --> 00:38:36,527
Don't worry.

909
00:38:36,529 --> 00:38:39,196
Your mother and sister will
be joining you in death. <font color="#d900d9">(GROANS)</font>

910
00:38:40,398 --> 00:38:42,032
Aah!

911
00:38:42,034 --> 00:38:45,702
<font color="#d900d9">(GROANING)</font>

912
00:38:45,704 --> 00:38:47,070
<font color="#d900d9">(BEEPING CONTINUES)</font>

913
00:38:47,072 --> 00:38:50,857
<font color="#d900d9">(POWERS DOWN)</font>

914
00:38:50,859 --> 00:38:53,744
<font color="#808080">FELICITY:</font>
Oliver, Lance did it.

915
00:38:53,746 --> 00:38:56,663
It's over.

916
00:38:56,665 --> 00:38:59,716
If I've learned anything
as a successful businessman,

917
00:38:59,718 --> 00:39:01,418
it's... <font color="#d900d9">(EXHALES SHARPLY)</font>

918
00:39:01,420 --> 00:39:02,702
<font color="#d900d9">(COUGHS)</font>

919
00:39:02,704 --> 00:39:04,421
Redundancy.

920
00:39:04,423 --> 00:39:06,757
<font color="#d900d9">(GROANS)</font>

921
00:39:06,759 --> 00:39:10,010
<font color="#d900d9">(ELECTRICITY HUMMING)</font>
<font color="#808080">OLIVER:</font> There's another device.

922
00:39:10,012 --> 00:39:12,062
There's two of them.

923
00:39:12,064 --> 00:39:14,231
<font color="#d900d9">(EXPLOSION)</font>

924
00:39:14,233 --> 00:39:17,768
Oliver Queen came back to right
<i>his father's wrongs.</i>

925
00:39:20,021 --> 00:39:24,358
<i>He couldn't have imagined</i>
<i>how severe they were.</i>

926
00:39:25,160 --> 00:39:28,028
<font color="#808080">LAUREL:</font> Go. Go!

927
00:39:28,030 --> 00:39:30,730
Uhh! Aah!

928
00:39:32,083 --> 00:39:33,250
<i>He returned to a city</i>

929
00:39:33,252 --> 00:39:35,953
<i>suffocated by corruption</i>
<i>and violence...</i>

930
00:39:35,955 --> 00:39:37,571
Laurel!

931
00:39:37,573 --> 00:39:38,738
The damage seems to be
contained

932
00:39:38,740 --> 00:39:41,208
on the east side.
Laurel.

933
00:39:41,210 --> 00:39:42,543
Go. Go, go, go.

934
00:39:42,545 --> 00:39:44,744
<i>And he fought</i>
<i>to make it better...</i>

935
00:39:44,746 --> 00:39:47,130
Please! Help me!

936
00:39:47,132 --> 00:39:50,851
<i>To make the people around him</i>
<i>better.</i>

937
00:39:50,853 --> 00:39:53,854
<font color="#d900d9">(STRAINED VOICE)</font> Tommy.
What are you doing here?

938
00:39:53,856 --> 00:39:55,973
I love you.

939
00:39:57,225 --> 00:40:00,227
<i>True heroism is defined</i>
<i>by sacrifice...</i>

940
00:40:00,229 --> 00:40:02,646
<font color="#d900d9">(GRUNTS)</font> Go! Go!
I'm right behind you!

941
00:40:02,648 --> 00:40:04,281
Dad!

942
00:40:04,283 --> 00:40:05,616
<i>And real heroes...</i>

943
00:40:05,618 --> 00:40:07,451
No!
No, Laurel!

944
00:40:08,403 --> 00:40:10,404
<i>Are the ones</i>
<i>who give up the most.</i>

945
00:40:10,406 --> 00:40:13,273
Come on. It's too late!
It's too late. <font color="#d900d9">(SOBBING)</font>

946
00:40:15,793 --> 00:40:17,911
<font color="#d900d9">(SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)</font>

947
00:40:17,913 --> 00:40:19,079
Tommy.

948
00:40:19,081 --> 00:40:20,914
<font color="#d900d9">(WHISPERING)</font>
Is... is Laurel safe?

949
00:40:20,916 --> 00:40:22,216
Is Laurel safe?

950
00:40:22,218 --> 00:40:24,718
Yeah. You saved her.

951
00:40:24,720 --> 00:40:26,253
I'm... I'm sorry.

952
00:40:26,255 --> 00:40:28,255
<font color="#d900d9">(VOICE BREAKS)</font> No.

953
00:40:28,257 --> 00:40:30,090
Don't apologize.

954
00:40:31,593 --> 00:40:32,809
And... no.

955
00:40:34,395 --> 00:40:37,147
Tommy. <font color="#d900d9">(CRYING)</font>

956
00:40:37,149 --> 00:40:39,983
<i>After the tragedy</i>
<i>in the Glades,</i>

957
00:40:39,985 --> 00:40:40,985
<i>we must wonder...</i>

958
00:40:40,986 --> 00:40:42,569
<font color="#d900d9">(WHISPERS)</font> Open your eyes.

959
00:40:42,571 --> 00:40:46,523
<i>What will Oliver Queen</i>
<i>become now?</i>

960
00:40:46,525 --> 00:40:50,327
<i>Something else yet again?</i>

961
00:40:50,329 --> 00:40:52,663
<i>Perhaps something...</i>

962
00:40:52,665 --> 00:40:54,197
<i>Better.</i>

963
